  "statement": {
    "ambiguity_status": "minor",
    "intended": "Let $\\frac{a_1}{b_1},\\frac{a_2}{b_2},\\ldots$ be the Farey fractions of order $n\\geq 4$. Let $f(n)$ be the largest integer such that if $1\\leq k<l\\leq k+f(n)$ then $\\frac{a_k}{b_k}$ and $\\frac{a_l}{b_l}$ are similarly ordered - in other words,\\[(a_k-a_l)(b_k-b_l)\\geq 0.\\]Estimate $f(n)$ - in particular, is there a constant $c>0$ such that $f(n)=(c+o(1))n$ for all large $n$?",
    "intended_statement_status": "source_text_pending_theorem_level_audit",
